      • localClusteringCoefficients

        public <V extends Vertex> gnu.trove.map.hash.TObjectDoubleHashMap<V> localClusteringCoefficients(Collection<V> vertices)
        Calculates the local clustering coefficient of each vertex in vertices. The local clustering coefficient is defined as:
        • C = 0 if k = 0 or k = 1,
        • C = 2y/k*(k-1) if k > 1, where y is the number of edges connecting neighbors of the vertex.
        Parameters:
        vertices - a collection of vertices the local clustering coefficients are to be calculated.
        Returns:
        an object-double map containing the vertex as key and the clustering coefficient as value.
